# Step-011 Scope Lock Remains Obstructed Without A Baseline Cash-Out And Gain Threshold In The Same Burden Currency

Status: `VERIFIED` Step-011 verdict with `INFERRED` missing-piece diagnosis

Step-011 narrows the branch, but it does not earn a Step-2-ready scope lock.

The remaining obstructions are load-bearing:

- no dedicated exact dyadic energy/helicity identity sheet was found for the
  chosen `dyadic coupled fluxes` package;
- the baseline stays at burden-language level instead of becoming one explicit
  inequality, exclusion statement, or contradiction line on the chosen ledger;
- the minimum gain threshold is still only "strictly positive after mixed
  helicity, pressure, viscosity, and localization debt," rather than one
  frozen quantitative currency on that same burden.

That combination means the branch has not yet frozen the same-currency
baseline and threshold that the later coercivity gate would have to beat.

So the correct filing is:
`scope lock still obstructed at Step 1`, even though the branch now has one
best burden family, one best first package, and one concrete Tao-sensitive
packet screen.

